          "title": "PRECLOUD",
          "summary": "Infrastructure code deployments often fail due to mismatched constraints over resource fields between the infrastructure code, the deployment engine, and the target cloud. precloud is a command line interface that contains rules that check for names, quotas, and resource-specific constraints to make sure that infrastructure code is deployed successfully. It can be used to harden deployments, enforce organizational resource patterns, and maintain security standards.",
